  <Subject Subject_ID="300189710">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300025427</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>administrators [300025427], people in administration and government [300025426], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to those who hold a particular office, post, or place of authority in a hierarchical organization, including civil, governmental, or private administrative contexts. For those holding positions of authority or command in the armed forces, use "military officers."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para aquellos que cumplen una función de confianza y autoridad dentro de un contexto civil, gubrenamental o administrativo privado. Para aquello que poseen posiciones de autoridad y comandancia en las fuerzas armadas, use "oficial (oficial militar)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor personen die een vertrouwens- en gezaghebbende positie bekleden in civiel, overheids- of particulier bestuur. Gebruik 'officieren' voor personen die gezaghebbende of leidinggevende posities in het leger bezitten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指在民間、政府或私人行政背景環境中擔任要職的人。對於在軍中擔任要職或指揮職務的人，則用「軍官 (軍事官員)」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
